                            <comment id="17430104" author="brandon.williams" created="Mon, 18 Oct 2021 17:19:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think before &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-16581&quot; title=&quot;Failure to execute queries should emit a KPI other than read timeout/unavailable so it can be alerted/tracked&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-16581&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-16581&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; these exceptions were just ignored since they weren&apos;t ProtocolExceptions but now the catchall is logging this warning and causing the teardown failures. Patch to log native IO errors like these at trace instead.&lt;/p&gt;

